This spontaneous report was received by UCB (Local event number: 2015US003051) from a consumer on 03-Mar-
2015 via Social media (facebook). 
This case concerns a 15-months-old male patient from United States of America.
Patient medical history included crohn s disease.
Concomitant drugs included steroids, Benadryl, cream and oatmeal baths.
On an unknown date the patient was initiated with Keppra (levetiracetam) film coated tablet at an unknown dose for
an unknown indication.
On an unknown date, the patient had a very bad allergic reaction to the medicine he was on for his colon, but it was
